{
  "stem": "6076.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Schloima, ?] we called him [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Schloima. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was a-- in America, I will say ritual slaughterer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I will explain to you what a ritual slaughterer really means.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A ritual slaughterer means in Hebrew, we say [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SPEAKING HEBREW] means the man has to have the same education like a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He calls himself a rabbi, but he has a trait which he becomes a [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What is a [SPEAKING HEBREW]?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The [SPEAKING HEBREW] is he has to have his skill, his education-- how to-- to-- kill that-- the cow, to kill the animal with such a fast movement that the cow, the animal, shouldn't feel no pain.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This goes back about in the-- now, in religious time, about 2,000 years ago when the [NON-ENGLISH] made that law.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I really didn't read the Bible for where it comes from.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I remember as the little girl how my father used to sharpen the knife.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a long narrow knife, very long and narrow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he used to sharpen that knife for hours.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he used to check that knife on his nail how sharp that knife was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I used to get sometimes dizzy to look how my father used to, you know, test it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And sometimes I feared that he shouldn't cut his nail to see how sharp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When it was sharp enough, then he stopped it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he had a few knives, a special knife for the chicken, a special knife for a-- for a duck, for-- for-- for goose, you know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you know, I remember all this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But he had to be learned and have the skills and be very educated in that-- that-- his profession.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
